00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:57.390
\b0 \cf0 So these are disabled folks using
technology to access the public world. Disabled

00:04:57.390 --> 00:05:05.330
people participate in and contribute to the
world by using innovative technologies to

00:05:05.330 --> 00:05:11.139
bridge the gap between their distinctive ways
of being in the world and a material and a

00:05:11.139 --> 00:05:16.960
social environment that's built for standard
bodies but we sometimes call and I like this

00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:19.509
term a lot "majority bodies".
\b [Laughter]

00:05:19.509 --> 00:05:25.900
\b0 The writer and the intellectual Helen
Keller, for example, used a human interpreter

00:05:25.900 --> 00:05:31.620
to facilitate communication. She's a 1908
graduate of Radcliffe, by the way, whereas

00:05:31.620 --> 00:05:39.880
as the physicist Stephen Hawking uses a machine
for communication and mobility.\

00:05:39.880 --> 00:05:45.879
Most technology that human beings use exclude
people with disabilities because the designs

00:05:45.879 --> 00:05:54.189
are either inflexible or only support standard
bodies. In our contemporary moment, however,

00:05:54.189 --> 00:06:01.319
distinctive technologies designed to be used
by people with disabilities are emerging from

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:07.539
the developed world. For instance, and I hope
you're all following this, double amputee

00:06:07.539 --> 00:06:15.919
Oscar Pistorius uses fibre-carbon prosthetic
legs made down the road here at MIT to compete

00:06:15.919 --> 00:06:23.020
against runners with fleshly legs and he is
trying to qualify to run in the Olympics,

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:29.810
not the Paralympics and has until I think
three or four days to do it. \

00:06:29.810 --> 00:06:35.629
To suggest the expansion and the evolution
of an accessible technology, I'm going to

00:06:35.629 --> 00:06:43.500
lay out for you today as I suggested two opposing
kinds of what I call World Building. Both

00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:49.569
are material and historical initiatives that
shaped communities by determining who and

00:06:49.569 --> 00:07:00.539
who does not participate in these communities.
One of these is eugenic world building. The

00:07:00.539 --> 00:07:05.240
other is inclusive world building. And I'm
going to start with eugenic world building

00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:10.370
but I'm going to emphasize the inclusive world
building but I want to spend a little bit

00:07:10.370 --> 00:07:15.659
of time laying out a contrast here so that
you have a sense of the logic and the history

00:07:15.659 --> 00:07:23.590
of what I called eugenic world building. \
So eugenic world building was a progressive

00:07:23.590 --> 00:07:28.499
and this is important, initiative carried
out primarily in the first half of the 20th

00:07:28.499 --> 00:07:35.810
century worldwide but most fully in the developed
West that's because they had technology and

00:07:35.810 --> 00:07:45.249
delivered -- I'm sorry. That is intended to
shape a desired citizenry by producing more

00:07:45.249 --> 00:07:50.289
of the people that any given group considers
as valuable and by eliminating the people

00:07:50.289 --> 00:07:56.639
that are considered to inferior. So things
like Better Baby Contests and Fitter Family

00:07:56.639 --> 00:08:03.659
Competitions were common practices to define
and to show what a desired citizen might be

00:08:03.659 --> 00:08:10.870
like. These are examples this Better Baby
Contests of what is sometimes called positive

00:08:10.870 --> 00:08:17.090
eugenics. \
Negative eugenics was carried out, of course,

00:08:17.090 --> 00:08:22.099
at the same time through laws and medical
practices in the United States and elsewhere

00:08:22.099 --> 00:08:28.249
in the developed world through primarily forced
sterilization which happened extensively in

00:08:28.249 --> 00:08:36.150
the United States. The famous 1927 Supreme
Court decision authorized forcible sterilization.

00:08:36.150 --> 00:08:44.560
Supreme Court Justice Oliver Wendell Holmes
explained the logic of this negative eugenics

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:51.830
policy by asserting quite famously the quote
"Three generations of imbeciles is enough."

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:58.340
\
Nazi Germany enacted, of course, the ultimate

00:08:58.340 --> 00:09:06.920
logic of negative eugenics beginning in September
1939 by rounding up and exterminating several

00:09:06.920 --> 00:09:12.140
hundred thousand disabled Germans who were
in institutions that range from orphanages

00:09:12.140 --> 00:09:17.870
to medical care facilities. They transferred
them to extermination facilities with the

00:09:17.870 --> 00:09:24.290
Nazi's in cooperation with medical practitioners
developed the gas chambers and the sham medical

00:09:24.290 --> 00:09:31.120
exams which were later used in a much more
ambitious Nazi project to exterminate the

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:38.470
Jews of Europe and other groups who were considered
to be eugenically inferior. \

00:09:38.470 --> 00:09:47.670
Today, across the developed world, reproductive
technologies carry out a kind of negative

00:09:47.670 --> 00:09:54.200
eugenics aimed at eliminating disability and
people born with disabilities under the logic

00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:58.850
of individual choice and we might want to
think a little bit about the more recent development

00:09:58.850 --> 00:10:04.200
of the population imbalance that's taking
place in developing countries as a result

00:10:04.200 --> 00:10:10.030
of sex selection abortion which is in some
sense the eugenic undertaking.\

00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:11.030
